events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Kenny Stills reached high to grab a 37-yard touchdown pass from Landry Jones midway through the fourth quarter for the tiebreaking score as the top-ranked Sooners beat No. 5 Florida State 23-13 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 1 Sooners stop Seminoles

events.name: North Texas Mean Green at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Trent Richardson and Eddie Lacy each had two long touchdown runs and career rushing highs and No. 2 Alabama's defense smothered North Texas in a 41-0 victory Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Richardson, No. 2 Alabama roll over N. Texas

events.name: Stanford Cardinal at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: No. 6 Stanford 37, Arizona 10
headlines.shortLinkText: Luck, Stanford top Arizona

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Northern Illinois Huskies

headlines.description: Russell Wilson threw for 347 yards and three scores, Montee Ball rushed for another two touchdowns and No. 7 Wisconsin piled up more than 600 yards of total offense Saturday in a 49-7 rout of Northern Illinois at Soldier Field.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wisconsin routs N. Illinois

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Tulsa Golden Hurricane

headlines.description: Brandon Weeden threw for 369 yards and three touchdowns, Joseph Randle ran for 128 yards and three more scores and No. 8 Oklahoma State beat Tulsa 59-33 in a game that didn't start until after midnight.
headlines.shortLinkText: After midnight, Oklahoma St. lets it all hang out

events.name: Idaho Vandals at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Cyrus Gray had three touchdowns and 101 yards rushing, Ryan Tannehill threw for 337 yards and two scores in less than three quarters and Texas A&M shook off a sloppy start for the 37-7 win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas A&M starts sloppy before drubbing Idaho

events.name: Navy Midshipmen at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Marcus Lattimore ran for a career-high 246 yards and three touchdowns to help No. 10 South Carolina hang on for a 24-21 victory over Navy on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lattimore leads Gamecocks

events.name: Washington Huskies at Nebraska Cornhuskers

headlines.description: Taylor Martinez threw for two touchdowns and ran for a third, and No. 11 Nebraska held off Washington for a wild 51-38 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nebraska 3-0 after rout of UW

events.name: Missouri State Bears at Oregon Ducks

headlines.description: LaMichael James ran for 204 yards and three touchdowns, including a 90-yarder, and No. 12 Oregon cruised to a 56-7 victory over Missouri State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: James runs for 204 as Oregon clubs Missouri St.

events.name: Arkansas State Red Wolves at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Logan Thomas threw for 292 yards and two touchdowns and No. 13 Virginia Tech overcame a sluggish offensive performance for a 26-7 victory over Arkansas State 26-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Virginia Tech shakes slow start to stifle Ark. St.

events.name: Troy Trojans at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: No. 14 Arkansas 38, Troy 28
headlines.shortLinkText: Wingo's 3 TDs lead Arkansas past pesky Troy

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Notre Dame Fighting Irish

headlines.description: Cierre Wood ran for two touchdowns, freshman George Atkinson III returned a kickoff 89 yards for a score and Robert Blanton had a late interception Saturday as Notre Dame beat No. 15 Michigan State 31-13 for its first win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notre Dame upends Michigan St.

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Florida Gators

headlines.description: Chris Rainey had 233 total yards, including an 83-yard touchdown catch, and No. 16 Florida beat rival Tennessee 33-23 Saturday and extended two decades of dominance in the Southeastern Conference series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rainey's 233-yard game leads Florida to win

events.name: Ohio State Buckeyes at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: Lamar Miller ran for 188 yards, Jacory Harris threw two first-quarter touchdown passes to Allen Hurns and Miami avoided matching its longest losing streak in 33 years by topping No. 17 Ohio State 24-6 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hurricanes bump Buckeyes

events.name: West Virginia Mountaineers at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Geno Smith threw for a career-high 388 yards, and No. 18 West Virginia withstood a furious comeback by Maryland to pull out a 37-31 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith lifts WVU past Maryland

events.name: Stephen F Austin Lumberjacks at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III continued his sterling start to the season and the No. 19 Baylor Bears celebrated their highest ranking since October 1991 by routing Stephen F. Austin 48-0 Saturday in a game that was ended in the third quarter because of lightning.
headlines.shortLinkText: Baylor blitzes SFA for a lightning-shortened win

events.name: Florida A&M Rattlers at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: B.J. Daniels threw for a career-high 382 yards and four touchdowns, pacing No. 20 South Florida's 70-17 rout of Florida A&M on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: QB Daniels' career day paces S. Florida's romp

events.name: Auburn Tigers at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: No. 21 Auburn's luck ended Saturday along with its 17-game winning streak as Tajh Boyd threw for 386 yards and four touchdowns in Clemson's 38-24 victory over the defending national champions.
headlines.shortLinkText: Auburn 17-game win streak kaput

events.name: Arizona State Sun Devils at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Illinois sacked Arizona State's Brock Osweiler six times and turned one into a touchdown in a 17-14 win over the No. 22 Sun Devils on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois notches 6 sacks en route to upset of ASU

events.name: Louisiana Monroe Warhawks at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Greg McCoy returned the second-half kickoff 94 yards for a touchdown, and the TCU defense came up with a big play right after that as the 23rd-ranked Horned Frogs took control in a 38-17 victory over Louisiana-Monroe on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU tops La.-Monroe for 21st straight home win

events.name: Texas Longhorns at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: Case McCoy passed for 168 yards and two touchdowns, D.J. Grant made his first three career touchdown catches, and No. 23 Texas avenged last season's stunning home loss to UCLA with a 49-20 victory over the Bruins on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas cruises past UCLA

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Denard Robinson ran for 198 yards and accounted for three touchdowns, leading Michigan to a 31-3 win over Eastern Michigan on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Robinson runs for 198 to spark Michigan rout

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Temple Owls

headlines.description: Michael Zordich scored on a 1-yard run with 2:44 left to stretch Penn State's winning streak against Temple to 29 straight games in a 14-10 victory on Saturday at Lincoln Financial Field.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn State thwarts Temple to extend streak

events.name: Pittsburgh Panthers at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: James Vandenberg threw three touchdown passes in the fourth quarter and Iowa rallied from a 17-point deficit to stun Pittsburgh 31-27 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vandenberg's 3 TDs in 4th lift Iowa past Pitt

events.name: Southeast Missouri State Redhawks at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Robert Marve threw a touchdown pass and was nearly perfect in his return from a knee injury to help Purdue beat Southeast Missouri State 59-0 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Purdue cruises, notches first shutout since '04

events.name: Coastal Carolina Chanticleers at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray passed for three touchdowns and also ran for a score -- all in the first half -- and Georgia received a needed boost by overwhelming Coastal Carolina 59-0 on Saturday.
